<subSubSection id="C33D439EFFB3FFE4FF0AF9A705D3F89D" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B981015FFB3FFE4FF0AF9A705A6F9C5" blockId="16.[151,1437,1578,2035]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Head, pronotum and scutellum shiny black. Scutellum touched with two lateral spots and one apical spot, orangebrown. Forewings black with orange-brown spots.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B981015FFB3FFE4FF5AF9FF04E9F8B8" blockId="16.[151,1437,1578,2035]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB3FFE4FF5AF9FF061EF928" box="[199,371,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with rounded caudal margin, ventral area with short setae. Subgenital plate angularly produced on lateral margin near base with caudal angle rounded, surface with short hairlike setae. Style linear with well developed preapical lobe, apical apophysis short, thumblike. Connective with arms 0.33 as long as stem. Aedeagus simple, dorsal apodeme long, well developed, preatrium reduced, shaft curved dorsoanteriorly and slightly narrowed caudally, with large gonopore on ventral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B981015FFB3FFE4FF5AF8AB05D3F89D" blockId="16.[151,1437,1578,2035]" box="[199,702,1830,1855]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB3FFE4FF5AF8AB0671F89C" box="[199,284,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Length.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity id="4CDFBDF0FFB3FFE4FEF6F8AA0687F89C" box="[363,490,1831,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.199999999999999" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="4.199999999999999" valueMax="4.3" valueMin="4.1">4.1–4.3mm</quantity>
. Female: 4.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
