<subSubSection id="C33D439EFFB3FFE4FF5AF83B060DF850" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B981015FFB3FFE4FF5AF83B060DF850" blockId="16.[151,1437,1578,2035]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB3FFE4FF5AF83B0623F86C" bold="true" box="[199,334,1974,1999]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name refers to the mountain range where it has been collected namely Sahyadri range or 
<collectingRegion id="49E3DEF7FFB3FFE4FF28F856067DF851" box="[181,272,2011,2034]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Western</collectingRegion>
Ghats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D439EFFB2FFE5FF5AFF1A0271FF77" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B981015FFB2FFE5FF5AFF1A0271FF77" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB2FFE5FF5AFF1A0659FF13" bold="true" box="[199,308,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species has male genitalia similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFB2FFE5FC10FF140378FF13" box="[909,1045,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB2FFE5FC10FF140378FF13" box="[909,1045,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFB2FFE5FBD2FF140392FF13" authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[1103,1279,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoattenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB2FFE5FBD2FF140392FF13" box="[1103,1279,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. neoattenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however the aedeagus in the new species lacks the flanges present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFB2FFE5FC93FF3004F9FF77" box="[782,916,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB2FFE5FC93FF3004F9FF77" box="[782,916,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and dorsal keel in 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFB2FFE5FBF5FF300278FF77" authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[1128,1301,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoattenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFB2FFE5FBF5FF300278FF77" box="[1128,1301,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P. neoattenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
